\begin_layout Standard
In Indian agriculture,
 rice stands as a cornerstone,
 woven into the cultural and culinary fabric of the nation.
 Rice,
 beyond being a mere crop,
 holds profound significance as the staple food for millions,
 nourishing the diverse population spread across the length and breadth of the country.
 As we delve into the intricacies of rice production,
 this article aims to unravel fascinating facts and insights about the leading states that play pivotal roles in shaping Indian Agricultural landscape.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Here our study focuses mainly on the production of rice in major rice producing states through different financial years from 2016-17 to 2021-22.
\end_layout

